Pancake is a fast, simple and lightweight HTTP-Server written in PHP with acceleration for PHP-powered websites.

System requirements:

Linux (should also run on other unixoid, POSIX-compliant operating systems with some work)
PHP 5.3.0 or newer compiled with --enable-pcntl --enable-sysvmsg --enable-sockets (PHP 5.4 recommended!)
PECL yaml 1.1.0 or newer
DeepTrace 1.4 or newer (DeepTrace is bundled with Pancake for x86, x86_64 and ARM (armv6l, armv7l) processors)

Installing Pancake:

1. cd /usr/local/
2. git clone git://github.com/pp3345/Pancake/
3. cd Pancake/sys
4. chmod +x pancake.sh
5. cd ext
6. chmod +x *

Running Pancake:

/usr/local/Pancake/sys/pancake.sh

(as root, you may use sudo)

Compiling DeepTrace:

1. cd
2. git clone git://github.com/NeoXiD/DeepTrace
3. cd DeepTrace
4. phpize
5. ./configure
6. make
7. cp modules/DeepTrace.so /usr/local/Pancake/sys/ext/<arch>_<phpver>.so (for example x86_64_54.so for x86_64 and PHP 5.4)

